narratives.question_text:
What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
(Your anonymous response to this question may be viewed by Yale College students, faculty, and advisers to aid in course selection and evaluating teaching.)
comments: I learned and strengthened many skills, including singing, solfege, rhythm, transcription, harmonic dictation, and more.
I feel I improved as a musician in general and was able to hone skills that are very important to me.

narratives.question_text:
What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
(Your anonymous response to this question may be viewed by Yale College students, faculty, and advisers to aid in course selection and evaluating teaching.)
comments: There is lots of flexibility in the course to tailor the curriculum to the needs and interests of the students!

This course was excellent, especially after converting one of the meeting days to one on one sessions. I am astonished that Ethan took the extra time and energy to personalize material for his students. It was truly a treat. Not only did I learn quite a bit, it also made coming to class a joy.

narratives.question_text: Among the practices in this course geared toward learning during the COVID-19 pandemic, which succeeded and which could be improved? Please comment on course practices that allowed for virtual engagement. (Your anonymous response to this question may be viewed by Yale College students, faculty, and advisers to aid in course selection and evaluating teaching.)
comments: What was extremely successful was having once and week full class meetings and once a week individual meetings to boost student engagement and make the the most of the course's flexibility.

narratives.question_text:
Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
(Your anonymous response to this question may be viewed by Yale College students, faculty, and advisers to aid in course selection and evaluating teaching.)
comments: Absolutely! This course was a great way to engage with music skills in a comfortable, fun environment.
Absolutely! I would recommend this class to anyone looking to become a better musician.

narratives.question_text: Please list any other mode(s) of learning, including any combination or variation of the above options.
comments: The class was very small, so it often had a seminar feel. We also had one on one weekly meetings with Ethan.
